<%- include('../../partials/implementer-core.md.ejs', { specificsBlock: `## Python Specifics

### Type Annotations
- Add explicit type annotations to every function parameter and return type — no bare \`def foo(x)\`.
- Use \`from __future__ import annotations\` for forward references; prefer \`X | Y\` unions (Python 3.10+).
- Use \`TypeVar\` and \`Generic\` for reusable typed containers; avoid \`Any\` from \`typing\`.

### Pydantic Models
- Define all request/response schemas as \`pydantic.BaseModel\` subclasses with field validation.
- Use \`model_validator\` / \`field_validator\` for cross-field and format constraints.
- Never accept raw \`dict\` at trust boundaries — parse into a model first.

### Async
- Prefer \`async def\` for I/O-bound functions; use \`asyncio.gather\` for concurrent fan-out.
- Never block the event loop with synchronous I/O — use \`asyncio.to_thread\` for CPU or legacy sync calls.

### Testing
- Use \`pytest\` with \`pytest-asyncio\` for async tests; prefer \`httpx.AsyncClient\` for HTTP integration tests.
- Parametrize with \`@pytest.mark.parametrize\` instead of copy-pasting test bodies.

### Anti-patterns to avoid
- Never use mutable default arguments (\`def foo(items=[]):\`).
- Never silence exceptions with bare \`except: pass\`.
- Never use \`eval\` or \`exec\` on untrusted input.
- Never import \`*\` from a module in production code.
- Never use \`assert\` for runtime validation — use explicit \`raise ValueError\`.` }) %>
